The paper focuses on object detection in the context of automatic driving, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach involves extracting features and using machine learning techniques to re-rank object proposals, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of semantic segmentation and CNN-based objectness also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the evaluation of the approach is done on the KITTI benchmark, which is a popular dataset for computer vision and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
